      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "With the exception of the first starter, BUZZOFFSKI (5) beat every one of these last time, and meets many better at the weights. Went forward and proved too strong scoring by 1.5 lengths over 1200m here. Has the light weight again and looks the measuring stick. VALLEY STAR (1) scored at Devonport Synthetic two back then finished runner-up to BUZZOFFSKI. Racing well and looks a key chance. MOMENTSLIKETHESE (6) was well in commission when resuming and finished third in the same race. Better draw and should be in the finish again. ALL INTRIQUE (7) finished 7 lengths away in the same race. Meets winner worse at weights but at top and drawn the inside. ONYX CHARM (3) was fifth in that event. Fitter and can sneak into the finish.",
